definition: to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be

sentences.english: You can use fun ice-cube shapes for drinks, too.
sentences.chinese: 同時，你也可以用些有趣的冰塊狀給飲料添加吸引力。

sentences.english: I can resist everything except temptation" is a very interesting epigram ."
sentences.chinese: “除了誘惑我什麼都能夠抵制”是句非常有趣的雋語。

sentences.english: "This project was interesting for manyreasons, "says Mr. Rochon.
sentences.chinese: 很多原因使得這個項目的很有趣，“羅雄先生說。

sentences.english: The most interesting thing was to climb the Fragrant Mount.
sentences.chinese: 最有趣的事情莫過於爬香山了。

sentences.english: Very well written, the book is packed with clever ideas and fascinating information.
sentences.chinese: 這本書有很好的文筆，聰明的想法以及有趣的信息。

sentences.english: The former scene by dinosaur was more wonderful than human's.
sentences.chinese: 剛退場的恐龍戲碼，就比我們精彩有趣得多了。

sentences.english: The most interesting thing was that there are two red bridal sedan chairs in the front door.
sentences.chinese: 最有趣的是，在前門有兩個紅色的新娘花轎。

sentences.english: Intriguingly, this could mean the device is even older than thought.
sentences.chinese: 有趣的是，這意味着這個裝置可能比想象的還要古老。

sentences.english: But it's exciting, it's definitly exciting to me.
sentences.chinese: 但這卻十分有趣，特別是對我來說。

sentences.english: You get to meet all sorts of really weird, interesting people.
sentences.chinese: 你會遇到各種奇怪又有趣的人。

sentences.english: And there's loads of interesting things to do, so.
sentences.chinese: 那裏還有很多有趣的事情可以做。

sentences.english: Beral thinks a more interesting candidate for study is prolactin .
sentences.chinese: 貝拉爾認爲，一個更爲有趣的研究課題是泌乳刺激素。

sentences.english: Some years Non-Vintage can be more fun.
sentences.chinese: 一些年頭，非葡萄酒釀造會更有趣。

sentences.english: The incidents are of a more external kind, but very funny.
sentences.chinese: 這些插曲屬於非常表面化的那種，但是十分有趣。

sentences.english: Your job is just to figure out how to make it fun and interesting.
sentences.chinese: 你的工作就是找到令它們有趣兒的方法。

sentences.english: His paintings and postcards are always thought-provoking and at the same time quite funny to look at.
sentences.chinese: 他的圖畫和卡片在發人深省的同時看着還相當的有趣。

definition: to be playful/to be fond of one's fun
erhua variant of 好玩[hao3 wan2]
to amuse/to make sb laugh/to tease
comical/funny/amusing/old pr. [gu3 ji1]/huaji, a form of comedy performance popular in Shanghai, Jiangsu and Zhejiang
